The paper deals with straggler-resistant multiplication of large matrices in distributed computing systems, which is a problem in distributed computing. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves coding techniques, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of cuboid partitioning and hierarchical coding involves optimization and algorithmic techniques, which could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper presents experimental results, which could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
